), a physical event, i.e., a conformational change in GSTP1-1 structure, follows the binding of the substrates and is crucial for the Ïƒ-complex formation. [6] This conformational transition is strongly dependent on diffusion-controlled motion of active site regions. [7] Because NBDHEX retains the same benzoxadiazole ring as NBD-Cl, a similar conformational change might also be necessary in this case to enable the Ïƒ-complex formation, and this might be prevented by a lack of structural flexibility in the crystalline environment. [1] Nonetheless, the position of NBDHEX with respect to GSH is very interesting.
